@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Krystal_Kaves" where
you want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other
files or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 8 colours.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Krystal_Kaves
      runs fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga
      with a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  Your position is indicated by a blue human-like icon located at
the center of the 5 by 5 space display. To play, just click in the
general direction you want to move (you can also use the cursor
keys to move about in the game area). If a coloured crystal is
located next to your position, just move toward it to pick it up.

  4 types of coloured crystals are randomly placed in the game
area, and as shown in the table that appears at the right of the
game board; the topmost crystal type have the most value and give
100 points when found. The other displayed crystals decrease value
as they appear downward, giving respectively 10 points, 5 points
and 1 point. The crystal table also displays how many crystals of
each type have been found.

  You can leave the cavern anytime, as long as you have picked up
at least one crystal, otherwise, the exit door will not open...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

